<p>The <code>upper</code> function converts a string to uppercase.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}echo $sampleText | upper{close}</pre>
<p>Result: <b>{echo $sampleText | upper}</b></p>

<h2>Simple Text</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'hello world' | upper{close}</pre>
<p>Uppercase: <b>{echo 'hello world' | upper}</b></p>

<h2>Mixed Case</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'HeLLo WoRLd' | upper{close}</pre>
<p>All upper: <b>{echo 'HeLLo WoRLd' | upper}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}echo $email | before('@') | upper{close}</pre>
<p>Username uppercase: <b>{echo $email | before('@') | upper}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo $sampleText | left(10) | upper | trim{close}</pre>
<p>First 10 upper: <b>{echo $sampleText | left(10) | upper | trim}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo 'hello' | upper | left(1){close}</pre>
<p>First initial: <b>{echo 'hello' | upper | left(1)}</b></p>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Works with UTF-8 characters.</p>
